main event: Three unidentified flying objects were observed in the Nebraska area on 26 August 1965.
interesting points: Objects were seen with a theodolite, appearing to be twice the size of a pinhead and moving at a high rate of speed., Witnesses reported the objects became unevenly illuminated, flashing on and off., The objects were described as rotating and glowing, with one changing shape from circular to diamond., A group of nine witnesses observed the objects zig-zagging at a rapid rate of about 50 degrees per second., The sighting lasted approximately 15 minutes, with one object projecting a beam of light.
witness description: Civilian witnesses including a Sergeant and two civilians who were employees of a local telephone company.
